node.text: My dream to create a brand started when I was 14 years old.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Travis Lubinsky in San Diego, California. May be an image of 1 person, standing and sky.

node.text: Life is too short to play small!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Travis Lubinsky on July 25, 2021. May be an image of 1 person.

node.text:
I was 18 years old and full of dreams! 

Shortly after this photo was taken, I started an apparel manufacturing company at SDSU and my career began. 

I managed Dj’s, hosted fashion shows, built websites, partnered with celebrities, and eventually became the co-founder of @flexwatches 

This lead me to appearing on TV over a dozen times, running an e-commerce portfolio, and creating partnerships with companies like Shopify, WWE, and Disney. 

These days I am managing a portfolio that includes several e-commerce brands, a creative agency, a media group, real estate and a new restaurant - @palmys 

The bottom line is that nobody is an overnight success story. You have to put in the work and be patient. Don’t believe what you see on Instagram. 

I still don’t consider myself to be “successful”, but the 18 year old Trav would be proud of the journey.
